  "time_ut": 1662026730,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u2019\u2019\u0dbb\u0da7\u0dd9\u0dd2 \u0db8\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dd4 \u0dad\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca \u0dc0\u0da7\u0dca\u0da7\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0db6\u0dd1\u2019\u2019",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "\"People of the country can't be let down anymore\"",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "President Ranil Wickramasinghe said that it is important to take the necessary measures so that the standard of living of all the people does not fall further, just like rescuing the country from the debt crisis.",
        "The President mentioned this in the discussion held today (1) at the President's Office with the representatives of the International Monetary Fund who are in Sri Lanka.",
        "Mr. Peter Breuer, Head of the Debt Capital Market Division of the International Monetary Fund, officially announced to President Ranil Wickremesinghe in this discussion that the staff reached an agreement to provide an Extended Credit Facility (EFF) to Sri Lanka.",
        "This credit facility of 2.9 billion US dollars is to be provided subject to a 48-month agreement.",
        "\"This is the time when we declared the country bankrupt for the first time. It is important in the medium term to recover from bankruptcy and free the country from the debt crisis, as well as prevent further decline in the economic and social lifestyle of all social segments.",
        "The beginning will be difficult. But it is very important and we can achieve growth in moving forward. This is an important step in the history of our country. We are not only committed to achieving the goals we have been given. We must move forward after those goals. Let's change our minds to build an export-based economy. It will make it easier to carry out social welfare work.\u201d",
        "Our country had an economy that preserved our dignity. \"We should be free from debt as a nation and as an individual\" agrees with Buddhism. Late Prime Minister D.S. That was also Mr. Senanayake's policy. He committed to follow it."
      ],
